{{For|the district and neighbourhood in Chile|Talcahuano#Administration}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Estadio Las Higueras | nickname = | image = | caption = | coordinates = {{coord|36|45|20|S|73|06|26|W|display=inline,title|region:CL_type:landmark_source:dewiki}} | broke_ground = | built = 1960 | opened = {{Start date|1961|11|25}} | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = 2008 | owner = Siderugica Huachipato | operator = | surface = grass | capacity = 10,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = 110 x 70 m | acreage = | tenants = [[Club Deportivo Huachipato]] (1960-2008) | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''Estadio Las Higueras''' was a football [[stadium]] in [[Talcahuano]], [[Chile]]. It was the home ground of the [[Club Deportivo Huachipato]] until the current [[Estadio CAP]] opened in 2009. The stadium held 10,000 people, was built in 1960 and was demolished in 2008.
