{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Gymnastics Federation of Nigeria |abbrev = GFN |logo =GFN logo.png |logosize = 170px |sport = [[Gymnastics]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = [[Nigeria Olympic Committee]] |founded =1975 |aff = [[International Federation of Gymnastics|IFG]] |affdate = |region = [[African Gymnastics Union]] |regionyear = |headquarters = [[National Stadium, Abuja|National Stadium]], [[Abuja]], [[Nigeria]] |location = National Stadium Sport Complex |president = Adefemi Foluso |vicepresident = Mohammed Aliyu K.S. |secretary =Rita Akande |url = gfn-gymnastics.org |countryflag = Nigeria |more = }}
The '''Gymnastics Federation of Nigeria''' is the overall [[Sports governing body|governing body]] of the sports of [[gymnastics]] in [[Nigeria]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.premiumtimesng.com/sports/104993-gymnastics-federation-to-train-orphanage-kids-for-olympics.html|title=Gymnastics Federation to train orphanage kids for Olympics|work=[[Premium Times]]|date=27 October 2015|accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref> Established in 1975, the body is affiliated to the [[International Federation of Gymnastics]] with the mission of ‚Äúan all round development of gymnastics in Nigeria and beyond‚Äù.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gfn-gymnastics.org/hml/index.php/about-us|title=History of GFN|accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref>
