{{infobox country at games | NPC = LBA | NPCname = [http://www.unilsg.com/ Libyan Paralympic Committee] | games = Paralympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 1 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Libya|competition=Summer Paralympics|begin_year=1996|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Libya]]''' made its [[Paralympic Games]] d√©but as the Great Socialist People's [[Libyan Arab Jamahiriya]] at the [[1996 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Atlanta]], sending four representatives to compete in [[powerlifting]]. The country has competed at every edition of the [[Summer Paralympics]] since then, but has never taken part in the [[Winter Paralympics]]. Libyan delegations have always been fairly small: three judokas, two powerlifters and a volleyball team in 2000; two powerlifters in 2004; a powerlifter and two table tennis players in 2008.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=LBA&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Libya at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref>
Libya won its first&mdash;and so far only&mdash;Paralympic medal when [[Abdelrahim Hamed]] took bronze in the men's over 100kg in powerlifting in 2000, lifting {{convert|235|kg|lb}}.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=LBA&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Libya at the Paralympics], International Paralympic Committee</ref>
