{{Infobox rugby team | country = Papua New Guinea Under 20 | image = Papua New Guinea rugby.png | imagesize = 90px | union = Papua New Guinea Rugby Football Union | nickname = | coach = | from = | captain = | caps = | top scorer | pattern_la1 = | pattern_b1 = | pattern_ra1 = | leftarm1 = FFFF00 | body1 = FFFF00 | rightarm1 = FFFF00 | shorts1 = FF0000 | socks1 = FFFF00 | first = | bigwin = | bigloss = | World cup apps = | year = | best = }}
The '''Papua New Guinea national under-20 rugby union team''' is for [[Papua New Guinea]]n [[rugby union]] players aged 20 or under on January 1 of the year during which they are selected.<ref name = pngloop-2014/> The team has played at the [[World Rugby Under 20 Trophy|World Rugby U20 Trophy]] and also competes at the [[Oceania Under 20 Rugby Championship|Oceania U20 Championship]] as of 2015.<ref name = sched-2015/>
{{toc limit|3}}
Under 20 age grade rugby came into existence, as a result of the IRB combining the [[Under 19 Rugby World Championship]] and [[Under 21 Rugby World Championship]] into a single [[IRB Junior World Championship]] tournament.<ref>[http://www.irb.com/newsmedia/mediazone/pressrelease/newsid=278620.html IRB announces restructure of age grade tournaments]</ref>
==2009 Junior World Trophy== In April 2009, Kenya hosted the [[2009 IRB Junior World Rugby Trophy]]. PNG lost their first two matches against [[Romania national under-20 rugby union team|Romania]] and [[Chile national under-20 rugby union team|Chile]] before winning against [[South Korea national under-20 rugby union team|South Korea]]. The team finished sixth in the tournament after being defeated by [[Namibia national under-20 rugby union team|Namibia]] in the 5th place play-off by 48‚Äì43.<ref name = irb-2009/>
==2010 Junior World Trophy== The [[2010 IRB Junior World Rugby Trophy]] was held in Russia in May 2010. PNG lost their three pool matches against [[Italy national under-20 rugby union team|Italy]], [[Uruguay national under-20 rugby union team|Uruguay]], and [[Romania national under-20 rugby union team|Romania]]. The team finished eighth in the tournament after being defeated by [[Zimbabwe national under-20 rugby union team|Zimbabwe]] in the 7th place play-off by 46‚Äì22.<ref name = irb-2010/>
