[[image:South African Hang Gliding and Paragliding Assoc.gif|thumb|240px|right|SAHPA logo]]

'''SAHPA''' is an acronym for the South African Hang Gliding and Paragliding Association. SAHPA is the governing body for [[paragliding]], [[hang gliding]], [[powered paragliding]], [[powered hang gliding ]] and [[para-trikes]] in South Africa.<ref>[http://www.cloudbase.co.za/index.php?comp=content&id=17 Cloudbase Paragliding website September 2017]</ref>

All pilots that take part in these sports in [[South Africa]] must be licensed by SAHPA, as required by the [[South African Civil Aviation Authority]].

