{{Infobox venue | name = Stade de l'Aube | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = [[Image:Stade de l'Aube.jpg|300px]] | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = Avenue Robert-Schumann, [[Troyes]], [[France]] | coordinates = {{Coord|48.307561|4.098458|display=inline,title|format=dms|type:landmark_scale:6000}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1924 | renovated = 1956, 2004 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = AirFibr Hybrid Grass <ref>http://www.naturalgrass.com/en/realisations/aube-stadium-of-troyes-france/</ref> | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 20,400 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[Troyes AC]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''Stade de l'Aube''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Troyes]], [[France]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches, by [[Troyes AC]]. The stadium is able to hold 20,400 people <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/france/champagne_ardenne.shtml|title=Stadiums in France Champagne-Ardenne|publisher=Worldstadiums.com|accessdate=7 November 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111104012730/http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/france/champagne_ardenne.shtml|archivedate=4 November 2011|df=}}</ref> and was built in 1956.
In June 2013, the '''Stade de l'Aube''' is the first stadium to build its pitch using the AirFibr hybrid turf technology,<ref>{{cite web|title=Le stade de l'Aube joue les pr√©curseurs|url=http://www.estac.fr/newsite/news/8574/70/Le-Stade-de-l-Aube-joue-les-precurseurs.htm|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140717043420/http://www.estac.fr/newsite/news/8574/70/Le-Stade-de-l-Aube-joue-les-precurseurs.htm|archivedate=2014-07-17|df=}}</ref> developed by the French company Natural Grass.
